de.oaam.model.oaam.common

Interface Struct

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DataTypeA, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    StructImpl

    public interface Struct
extends DataTypeA
    A representation of the model object 'Struct'. A structure composed of multiple variables or arrays

    The following features are supported:

    • Alignment
    • Fields
    • Inherits From
    • Is Abstract
    See Also:
    CommonPackage.getStruct()

    • Method Detail

      • getAlignment

        int getAlignment()
        Returns the value of the 'Alignment' attribute. The default value is "8". The internal alignment (padding) of array fields in bits. 0 means all elements are directly after each other. Values above 0 mean that fields smaller than the value will be stuffed with padding bits until a multiple of the alignment value is reached. 8 equals a one Byte allignment.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Alignment' attribute.
        See Also:
        setAlignment(int), CommonPackage.getStruct_Alignment()

      • getInheritsFrom

        Struct getInheritsFrom()
        Returns the value of the 'Inherits From' reference. A reference to a super type of the struct. The inhereting struc will contain all elements of the super type and his super types plus the elements that are defined here.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Inherits From' reference.
        See Also:
        setInheritsFrom(Struct), CommonPackage.getStruct_InheritsFrom()

      • isIsAbstract

        boolean isIsAbstract()
        Returns the value of the 'Is Abstract' attribute. If set to true there cannot be an instance of that struct. However, inhereting structs may be used in tasks or signals.

        the value of the 'Is Abstract' attribute.
